rdt.section: Reference
title: $:/plugins/rimir/kind/doc/reference
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! Type tiddler fields

|!Field |!Required |!Description |
|`kind.type` |Yes |Unique type key. Instances of this type carry `kind.type: <this-value>`. |
|`kind.fields` |Yes |Stringified-JSON array of field definitions. See //Field def schema// below. |
|`kind.caption` |No |Display name shown in dropdowns, validator headings, etc. |
|`kind.icon` |No |Emoji or short text shown alongside the caption |
|`kind.namespaces` |No |Space-separated namespace memberships. Empty = visible only when active namespace is //(all)//. |
|`kind.parent-kinds` |No |Space-separated list of parent type-keys. Non-empty → ''child kind'' — hidden from global creation surfaces (in-tiddler creator's primary pill row, cascade-palette //Create entity// drill). Only creatable via the per-instance cascade-palette ''Create here…'' action on an existing instance of a kind in this list. Instance back-reference uses the standard `parent` field. Multi-valued for shared children (e.g. `journal training-log`). Validator flags instances whose `parent` is missing OR whose parent's `kind.type` isn't in this list. Editable as a free-text field in Type-builder, OR via a type-safe toggle picker in the cascade-palette //Manage kinds// drill (lists every kind except self, toggling commits to this field). |
|`kind.title-formula` |No |TW filter expression evaluated with `<target-tid>` as the source. Result becomes the new instance's title. Omit for manually-titled types. |
|`kind.auto-children` |No |JSON array. Each entry is `{"kind":"<child-type-key>","fields":{"<field>":"<value>",...}}`. When an instance of this type is saved (via any create path — in-tiddler //Creator// button, cascade-palette //+ New X//, ref-spawn from a `+ Create new …` row, or //Create here…//), each listed child instance is materialised with `parent` pre-set to the new parent's title + per-entry `fields` overrides + the child kind's normal field defaults applied. The child's `kind.title-formula` evaluates against the draft so it sees the back-ref. Entries referencing kinds that don't exist are skipped silently. NOT recursive — auto-children of auto-children don't fire automatically. Editable as raw JSON in Type-builder (3-row textarea), OR via a full CRUD drill in the cascade-palette //Manage kinds// drill — drill into ''auto-children (N)'', list of entries with a //+ Add auto-child entry…// picker, drill into an entry to edit per-field overrides (each as its own text-row, DEL removes the override) plus //+ Add field override…// picker filtered to fields not yet overridden, DEL on an entry-row removes the whole entry. No JSON typing required. |
|`kind.stream-fields` |No |Space-separated field keys shown in the stream-river field bar. Empty / missing = bar is invisible for instances of this type. |
|`kind.back-group-by` |No |Reverse-reference navigation (the ''Referenced by…'' action): field key whose value clusters this kind's instances in the listing (e.g. `status`). Empty = one undifferentiated group. |
|`kind.back-sort-by` |No |Reverse-reference navigation: field key the listing sorts by, ''descending'' (newest-first). Defaults to `modified`. |

!! Instance tiddler fields

|!Field |!Required |!Description |
|`kind.type` |Yes |The type key. Marks the tiddler as an instance. |
|Field keys from `kind.fields` |Per field's `constraints` |Each field's value is stored as a tiddler field with the name `<key>`. Multi-cardinality values are stored as space-separated lists (TW list-field convention). |

!! Field def schema (entries inside `kind.fields` JSON)

|!Property |!Required |!Description |!Applies to `typed` |
|`key` |Yes |Field key. Used as both the field name on instances and the identifier in `kind.stream-fields` / `kind.title-formula`. |all |
|`typed` |Yes |Editor kind. See //typed values// table. |all |
|`caption` |No |Display label. Falls back to `key` if absent. |all |
|`icon` |No |Emoji or short text. |all |
|`constraints` |No |Array of constraint strings. See //Constraints// table. |all (most relevant for editable types) |
|`options` |Required for `enum` |Array of option strings. |`enum` |
|`ref-types` |Optional for `ref` |Array of `kind.type` values whose instances may be referenced. When empty or absent, all kind-instances in the wiki are selectable (the type-builder displays //(any kind)//). |`ref` |
|`cardinality` |No (default `single`) |Either `single` or `multi`. Multi values are space-separated lists. |`enum`, `ref` |
|`formula` |Required for `$calculated` |Filter expression evaluated with `<target-tid>` as source. |`$calculated` |
|`default` |No |Filter expression evaluated against the draft (`<target-tid>`-as-source subfilter). Materialised onto each fresh instance for fields that would otherwise be blank, re-fired on ref/enum changes so dependent defaults populate after their dependencies are set. Examples: `[[planned]]` (static literal); `[<now "YYYY0MM0DD0hh0mm0ss0XXX">]` (current timestamp in TW canonical form — note single angle brackets in filter context, NOT `<<now …>>` which is wikitext-only); `[get[parent]get[caption]]` (reads parent's caption from the draft); `[get[parent]get[caption]] [[at]] [get[planned-at]format:date[0DD.0MM.YYYY 0hh:0mm]] +[join[ ]]` (composite — chain `+[join[X]]` for multi-item filters; otherwise only the first item is taken). User-typed values always win (the gate is `!has[<field>]`, not equality with the computed default). |text, longtext, number, date, datetime, url, email, phone, enum |
|`clone` |No |Set to `skip` to exclude this field from the ''+ Clone fields from existing'' copy in the cascade-palette creator (e.g. blank-out a journal `text` field on clone). Default = copy. Computed fields (`$title` / `$calculated`) are always excluded regardless. |all (most relevant on body / unique / computed-ish fields) |
|`back-nav` |No |Reverse-reference navigation: set to `no` to opt this `ref` field out of the ''Referenced by…'' drill (so referencing instances reached through it are not surfaced). Default = on. |`ref` |
|`back-label` |No |Reverse-reference navigation: override the entry-level row label for this relation when several incoming relations exist (default is //KindCaption (as FieldCaption)//, e.g. //Conversation (as Participants)//). |`ref` |

!! `typed` values

|!Value |!Editor |!Notes |
|`text` |single-line input |Free-form short string |
|`longtext` |textarea |Free-form long text |
|`number` |numeric input |Stored as string; validate as needed |
|`date` |TW date picker |TW date format |
|`datetime` |TW date picker w/ time |TW datetime format, 24h |
|`url` |Single-line input (`type="url"`) |Format-checked: must start with `http://` or `https://` (when non-blank) |
|`email` |Single-line input (`type="email"`) |Format-checked: `local@domain.tld` shape (when non-blank) |
|`phone` |Single-line input (`type="tel"`) |Format-checked for German numbers (`+49` or `0` prefix, when non-blank) |
|`enum` |`<$select>` or pill toggle |`options` required; honour `cardinality` |
|`ref` |Typeahead (search + dropdown + selected pills) |`ref-types` optional (empty = any kind-instance); honour `cardinality`; display via target tiddler's caption (falls back to title) |
|`$title` |Read-only |Marks the field as the title position; not editable. Title is computed from the type's `kind.title-formula`. |
|`$calculated` |Read-only |Display-only derived field; value computed from the field's `formula` |

!! Constraints

|!String |!Meaning |
|`required` |Field value must not be blank |
|`min:N` |Minimum N characters (text/longtext) or N entries (multi enum/ref) |
|`max:N` |Maximum N characters or entries |
|`unique` |Field value must not equal another instance of the same type's same field |
|`unique:wiki` |Field value must not equal any other tiddler's same field |

All constraints are blocking — they show up in red in the validator and disable the Create button in the creator.

!! Config tiddlers

|!Path |!Purpose |
|`$:/config/rimir/kind/active-namespace` |Active namespace; empty = all |
|`$:/config/rimir/kind/streambar-max-length` |Truncation threshold for the stream-view field bar (default 20) |
|`$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/edge-fields` |''Instances Overview'': ref-field keys drawn as edges, stored in the `edges` field (titlelist; ships defaulting to `parent`). The field is named `edges`, NOT `fields`: a custom field literally named `fields` collides with the TiddlyWeb sync wire-format's reserved `fields` container and is silently dropped on every browser→server save |
|`$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/hidden-types` |''Instances Overview'': type keys hidden from the graph (titlelist; empty/absent = all types shown) |
|`$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/structure` |''Instances Overview'': persisted node positions — data tiddler whose index keys are instance titles and values are `x,y` |
|`$:/config/rimir/kind/notes-preview/kinds` |''Notes'' side-preview: space-separated list of `kind.type`s to include as related notes (default `note`). Filters BOTH the `parent`-children and ref-referrer paths, so a non-note child (e.g. a conversation that has the instance as `parent`) is not listed. The instance's own content is always shown first regardless of its kind. Add type keys (e.g. `note p-note`) to widen. |
|`$:/config/rimir/kind/type-selector-enable` |Story-river ''type selector'': `yes`/`no` (default `yes`). When `yes`, tiddlers with no `kind.type` show a ''＋ type'' picker under the title to assign a kind. Typed tiddlers' field-bar type icon is a picker regardless of this setting. |
|`$:/config/rimir/kind/type-selector-filter` |Story-river ''type selector'': qualifying filter deciding which untyped tiddlers get the ''＋ type'' picker (default `[all[current]!is[system]!has[draft.of]]`). Evaluated with the tiddler as `all[current]`. |

!! State tiddlers

|!Path |!Purpose |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/draft/<type-key>` |Creator's draft for in-progress instance |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/instances-overview/search` |''Instances Overview'': node search-box text |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/graph-modal` |Graph tooltip modal mode switch — `edit` field (live editor for that instance), `delete` field (confirm dialog), or `kind-tid` + `host` fields (create-child form). Deleted on Close/Cancel/Create/Delete |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/graph-modal/draft` |Draft for the graph tooltip's ''Add child'' create form (parent pre-set, defaults applied; re-seeded on every tooltip button click) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/__graph-created` |Transient capture of the just-created tiddler title from the graph-modal create flow |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/context/direction` |''Context'' preview: parent-tree direction — `to` (descendants, default) or `from` (ancestors) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/context/depth` |''Context'' preview: number of `parent`-tree levels to show (1–5, default 2) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/context/edge-fields` |''Context'' preview: ref-field keys drawn as edges, stored in the `edges` field (titlelist; defaults to `parent`, and floors back to `parent` if every field is deselected) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/context/hidden-types` |''Context'' preview: type keys hidden from the graph (titlelist; empty/absent = all types shown) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/edit-mode/<target-tid>` |Per-instance toggle between popup and inline edit mode in stream-view |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/ta/<target-tid>/<field-key>` |Typeahead search-input state for a ref field |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/creator/selected-type` |Currently-selected type in the creator |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/type-builder/selected` |Currently-edited type in the type-builder |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/type-builder/preview-draft` |Live editor preview's target |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-draft/<type-key>` |Manage-kinds ''+ Create new instance'' draft (per type) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-preview-draft/<type-key>` |Manage-kinds side-preview form draft (per type — survives drill-in/out) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/notes/mode` |''Notes'' side-preview layout: `stream` (default) or `tabbed` |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/notes/active` |''Notes'' side-preview active tab (note title) in `tabbed` mode; self-heals to the instance when not in the current note set |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/notes/text-edit` |''Notes'' side-preview: which empty note (if any) is currently being initialised as a plain-`text` body via the ''✎ Text'' button; while set, that note renders an inline `$edit-text` textarea instead of its init buttons |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-spawn-draft/<parent-tid>/<parent-field>/<ref-type-key>` |Draft for a nested ''+ Create new <X>'' spawn from a ref-field picker (per spawn point — survives drill-in/out and supports arbitrary nesting depth) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/create-here-draft/<host-tid>/<target-field>/<ref-type-key>` |Draft for the ''Create here…'' per-instance action (parallel to the spawn draft, but the back-ref direction is inverted — host title is pre-set on the NEW instance's `<target-field>` rather than written to the host's field). |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/__spawn-result` |Transient capture of the just-spawned tiddler title (used by `kind.cascade-spawn-save` to wire into the parent's ref field) |
|`<create-here-draft-tid>/wizidx` |Current 1-based step index for a creation-wizard run (per draft; set to `1` on drill-open, bumped by ← Back / Next →, deleted on ✓ Create) |

!! Creation wizards (multi-step guided create)

A wizard turns the cascade-palette ''Create here…'' flow for a kind from one all-fields form into an ordered sequence of steps, each asking only the field(s) the designer assigns — so an inexperienced user is guided to a valid instance without ever opening //Edit fields//. Define one step per tiddler:

|!Field |!Required |!Meaning |
|tag |Yes |`$:/tags/rimir/kind/wizard-step` |
|`ca-wizard-kind` |Yes |Target type-key being created (e.g. `topic`). |
|`ca-wizard-context` |No |Host type-key this wizard variant applies to (e.g. `person` — the kind you launched ''Create here…'' from). Empty = the ''default'' wizard for the kind. Resolution per (target, host): the context-specific step set wins; if none exists, the default set is used. |
|`ca-order` |Yes |Step order within the wizard (numeric, `nsort`ed). |
|`ca-step-name` |Yes |Short prompt shown in the progress row (//Step n of m · <name>//). Avoid `"` in the value. |
|`ca-step-fields` |Yes |Space-separated field keys to ask for in this step. Each renders via the standard field editor (`kind.field-edit-json`) — text, enum, ref picker, date, etc. |
|`ca-step-hint` |No |Longer help text for the step. |
|`ca-step-date-default` |No |For a ''date'' field step: a smart-date / offset expr (e.g. `+2w`, `today`, `2026-07-01`) injected as the row's `ca-date-default`, so the palette pre-fills the still-blank field when the step's editor auto-opens. In edit mode the date can then be adjusted with `+/-` (Shift ±month, Ctrl ±year), typed, or picked from the calendar popup (if cascade-palette's `date-picker-module` is configured). |
|`ca-step-auto-edit` |No |`yes` forces a single-field step to auto-open its editor even when the field is already ''valid'' (normally only //invalid// steps auto-open; a valid step would instead auto-advance). Use for an ''optional'' field the user should still land in and consciously fill-or-skip — e.g. tickler's `until`: land in the (empty) date editor, ↵ on empty to continue (a single-date reminder) or set a date (a duration). |
|`ca-step-pick-tree` |No |`yes`\|`tree`\|`flat` turns a ''single-`ca-step-fields`'' ref step into the ''switchable'' picker (see below): a drillable namespace ''tree'' and a ''flat'' candidate list the user can flip between at runtime. The value is the //initial// layout (`yes`/`tree` → tree, `flat` → flat); absent = the plain flat field editor (no switch). Use on the //final// step (pick = create). |
|`ca-step-pick-roots` |No |Filter for the tree layout's root nodes. Default `$:/config/rimir/kind/wizard/pick-roots` = `[all[tiddlers]!is[system]cp-child-of[]]`. Children come from `$:/config/rimir/kind/wizard/pick-children` (= `cp-child-of<currentTiddler>`, the namespace tree). |

''Behaviour:'' the whole wizard is one drill stage backed by `<draft>/wizidx`. ''Next →'' is blocked (⛔ row) until the current step's fields pass `kind.viol-any`; the final ''✓ Create'' re-checks the whole draft via `kind.any-invalid` then runs `kind.finalize-create` (title-formula, validation, auto-children all behave as in the Creator). The launch context pre-seeds the back-ref (parent or ref field), but a `parent`/ref step lets the user redirect it. ''Esc'' cancels the whole wizard. ⚠️ Every ''required'' field of the kind must appear in some step (or carry a `default`), otherwise the final ''Create'' stays ⛔-blocked.

''Hands-free landing.'' A single-field step ''auto-opens'' its one input — a text/enum step lands directly in value-edit mode (Enter commits → Next), a ref/tree step lands directly in the picker (uses cascade-palette's `ca-auto` / `ca-auto-token`). A non-selectable heading bar above the input names each step (cascade-palette `ca-stage-heading` / `ca-next-heading`). So a guided create is mostly just ''type · Enter · pick · Enter''.

''Switchable picker'' (`ca-step-pick-tree: yes|tree|flat`). The step opens a parent/ref picker with ''two layouts'' the user flips between at runtime via a pinned ''⇄ Switch'' row at the top:
* ''Tree'' — a drillable hierarchy (same structure as the //By Namespace// view): ''Right-arrow'' descends into a node's children. Universe = the `cp-child-of` namespace tree (any tiddler), overridable via `ca-step-pick-roots` + the `pick-roots` / `pick-children` config tiddlers.
* ''Flat'' — the field's valid ref candidates (`kind.ref-candidates`, i.e. instances of the field's ref-types) as a single non-drillable list.

In ''both'' layouts ''Enter'' on a row commits it as the field value AND finalises the instance — choosing IS the create (`ca-enter-fires`) — each focused row shows its kind ''context graph'' in the side preview, and after the create the palette returns to the entity you launched ''Create here…'' from (`ca-after-fire: pop-to-actions`) rather than closing. The chosen layout is ''remembered per step'' in a persisted JSON-map config tiddler (`$:/config/rimir/kind/wizard/pick-mode`, keyed by step title), so a user's preference sticks across creates. The ⇄ row lives at the picker root; deep in the tree, back out (Esc) to reach it.

''Preferred spawn-locations'' (`kind.spawn-locations` on the launching instance). An instance can carry a `kind.spawn-locations` field — a list of tiddler titles — surfaced as ★-marked rows pinned to the ''top'' of the picker (above the ⇄ Switch row), in ''both'' layouts and ''regardless'' of which kind is being created. Picking a ★ row behaves exactly like picking any other node (commit + finalise + context graph + return-to-entity), giving one-keystroke placement into a frequent parent. One list per instance; set it via //Edit fields// / the field bar (add the addable ''Spawn locations'' common field, or write `kind.spawn-locations` directly). A location is not de-duplicated against its natural tree/list position — the ★ copy is the shortcut. Empty / missing field → no ★ rows (no change to the picker).

!! Engine functions (engine.tid)

|!Function |!Returns |
|`kind.types-all()` |All type tiddlers |
|`kind.locate-type(type-key)` |The type tiddler with that key |
|`kind.active-ns()` |Current active namespace string |
|`kind.belongs-to-ns(active-ns)` |Filter predicate; non-empty if `<currentTiddler>` is in scope |
|`kind.namespaces-all()` |Unique sorted list of all namespaces used by any type |
|`kind.field-keys(type-tid)` |Ordered list of field keys |
|`kind.field-typed(type-tid, field-key)` |`typed` value of the field |
|`kind.field-caption(type-tid, field-key)` |Field caption (falls back to key) |
|`kind.constraints(type-tid, field-key)` |All constraint strings |
|`kind.has-constraint(type-tid, field-key, name)` |Non-empty if constraint present |
|`kind.constraint-num(type-tid, field-key, prefix)` |Numeric value of `min:N` / `max:N` |
|`kind.options(type-tid, field-key)` |Enum option strings |
|`kind.ref-types(type-tid, field-key)` |Allowed ref target type keys |
|`kind.ref-candidates(type-tid, field-key)` |All currently-existing target instances. When `ref-types` is empty, falls back to all kind-instances in the wiki (any `kind.type`). |
|`kind.eval-title(type-tid, target-tid)` |Computed title for an instance |
|`kind.is-child-kind(type-tid)` `kind.parent-kinds-of(type-tid)` `kind.parent-kinds-include(type-tid, candidate)` |Child-kind predicates/getters. Non-empty if `kind.parent-kinds` is set. |
|`kind.top-level-types()` `kind.child-kinds-of(parent-key)` |Filtered views of `kind.types-all()` — top-level (no parent-kinds) vs children of a given parent type-key. |
|`kind.has-ref-field-to(type-tid, target-key)` `kind.ref-back-fields-of(type-tid, target-key)` `kind.kinds-with-back-ref-to(target-key)` |"Create here…" discovery — find kinds whose ref-typed fields list the target as a valid `ref-types` member, and the field-keys on those kinds. |
|`kind.create-here-target-kinds(host-key)` `kind.has-create-here-options(host-tid)` |Union of child kinds + ref-back kinds; the cascade-palette ''Create here…'' action's `ca-applies` gates on this. |
|`kind.referencing-instances(host-tid, source-tid, field-key)` |Reverse-reference core: instances of `source-tid`'s kind whose `field-key` references `host-tid`. The building block for the ''Referenced by…'' drill and any two-hop reverse lookup. |
|`kind.qual-source-kinds(host-tid)` `kind.qual-back-fields(host-tid, source-tid)` `kind.back-rel-count(host-tid)` |Reverse-nav discovery — which source kinds reference the host (through a `back-nav`-enabled field with ≥1 instance), the qualifying field-keys per source kind, and the total relation count (1 → skip straight to the instance list; ≥2 → entry-level relation rows). |
|`kind.back-sort-field-eff(source-tid)` `kind.inst-group-val(source-tid, inst-tid)` |Reverse-nav listing helpers — effective sort field (`kind.back-sort-by`, default `modified`) and an instance's group value (`kind.back-group-by`). |
|`kind.auto-children-array(type-tid)` `kind.auto-children-indexes(type-tid)` `kind.has-auto-children(type-tid)` |Raw access to the parent kind's `kind.auto-children` JSON array. |
|`kind.auto-child-kind-at(type-tid, idx)` `kind.auto-child-fields-at(type-tid, idx)` `kind.auto-child-field-value-at(type-tid, idx, field-key)` |Walk one entry — get the child kind's type-key, the field-key list, and individual field values that should override the child kind's defaults. |
|`kind.viol-required(...)` `kind.viol-min(...)` `kind.viol-max(...)` `kind.viol-unique(...)` `kind.viol-unique-wiki(...)` `kind.viol-title(...)` `kind.viol-format-url(...)` `kind.viol-format-email(...)` `kind.viol-format-phone(...)` `kind.viol-parent-kind(...)` |Validation predicates (non-empty = violation). `kind.viol-parent-kind` checks that a child kind's instance has a `parent` whose `kind.type` is in the kind's `parent-kinds` list. |
|`kind.any-invalid(type-tid, type-key, target-tid)` |Non-empty if any constraint is violated on any field |
|`kind.shorten`, `kind.display`, `kind.resolve-ref` |Display helpers |

!! Engine procedures (engine.tid)

|!Procedure |!Effect |
|`kind.compute-default(type-tid, field-key, target-tid)` |Evaluates the field's `default` filter against `<target-tid>`-as-source via `subfilter`. Returns the first result (or empty). Used by `apply-defaults-to` / `force-apply-defaults` and available to any other code that wants to preview the computed default. |
|`kind.apply-defaults-to(type-tid, target-tid)` |Stamps `kind.type` + walks all defaultable fields and writes `compute-default` onto `target-tid` for fields currently blank (idempotent — leaves user-set fields alone). Used by every create path before save, AND re-fired from field-input action chains after each ref/enum change so dependent defaults populate. |
|`kind.force-apply-defaults(type-tid, target-tid)` |Like `apply-defaults-to` but unconditional. Used by the //Reset to defaults// flow. |
|`kind.apply-auto-children(parent-tid, type-tid)` |Walks `type-tid.kind.auto-children` and materialises each entry as a new tiddler with `parent: <<parent-tid>>` + per-entry `fields` overrides + the child kind's own field defaults. Transcluded by `kind.finalize-create` //nested inside// its `$action-createtiddler`, with `parent-tid` taken from `<<createTiddler-title>>` (the real post-uniquification title — a sibling read of `$savetitle` is evaluated at render time and sees a stale value, so the nesting is load-bearing). Entries pointing at non-existent kinds are skipped silently. Not recursive. |

</$fill>
</$transclude>
